Flashcard(question: " Used to perform back end processes such as your bank transferring data or uploading video", answer: "Server Side"),
Flashcard(question: " Exploits the trust a site has in the user's browser. Tricks a user into sending unauthorized commands to a web application", answer: "Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF or XSRF)"),
Flashcard(question: " Web applications should have anti-forgery techniques such as a ___", answer: "Cryptographic Token"),
Flashcard(question: " An XSRF attacker can make a funds transfer request by emailing a ___ and hoping the victim is already logged in", answer: "Hyperlink"),
Flashcard(question: " Where attacker finds vulnerable web application, then web server performs requests on behalf of attacker", answer: "Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)"),
Flashcard(question: " To prevent SSRF the server should always validate the ___ to the server and the ___", answer: "Input Output"),
Flashcard(question: " In SSRF the attacker will send a request to the server that will require it to perform ___ in the background", answer: "Another Function"),
Flashcard(question: " In the Capital One attack the ___ was misconfigured allowing it to be queried and gather information", answer: "WAF (Web Application Firewall)"),
Flashcard(question: " Traditional anti-virus software is very good at stopping ___ vulnerabilities", answer: "Known"),
Flashcard(question: " Drivers are a perfect conduit for a malware attack because they are ___ by your operating system", answer: "Trusted"),
Flashcard(question: " Used on operating system, such as Windows compatibility mode (backwards compatibility)", answer: "Shimming"),
Flashcard(question: " Malware authors can write their ___ to get around security such as Windows User Account Control", answer: "Own Shims"),
Flashcard(question: " When your system downloads malware it is downloading a unique version that won't match signatures in your antivirus software", answer: "Refactoring (Metamorphic Malware)"),
Flashcard(question: " In refactoring the attacker makes the malware ___ every time", answer: "Appear Different"),
Flashcard(question: " To detect refactoring you need to use a ___ rather than signature-based detection", answer: "Layered Approach"),
Flashcard(question: " Combines an on-path attack with a downgrade attack;", answer: "Difficult to implement, but big returns for the attacker"),
Flashcard(question: " For SSL stripping, attacker sits in the ___ of the conversation between client and server", answer: "Middle"),
Flashcard(question: " Proxying", answer: "Sitting in the middle of attack to modify communication between web site visitor and web server"),
Flashcard(question: " In SSL stripping attacker ___ request for HTTPS by web server and sends it back to web server", answer: "Intercerpts"),
Flashcard(question: " In SSL stripping after attacker sends back HTTPS request it will set up an ___ between only the attacker and web server", answer: "Encrypted Channel"),
Flashcard(question: " In SSL stripping after attacker has established the encrypted channel he will send the ___ back to website visitor", answer: "Non-Encrypted Page"),
Flashcard(question: " In SSL stripping website visitor has ___ that any changes were made in the middle", answer: "No Idea"),
Flashcard(question: " In SSL stripping if website visitor sends the ___ and ___ the attacker can see it and log in with the credentials", answer: "Username Password"),
Flashcard(question: " Race Condition", answer: "Multiple threads trying to interact with the same system at the same time. i.e. husband and wife both trying to withdraw from same account at same time."),
Flashcard(question: " TOCTOU attack", answer: "Checking for things to occur on a system and making changes knowing there might be other changes happening"),
Flashcard(question: " Memory Leak", answer: "Memory never returns to system, so system uses more and more until it uses all of it and crashes system"),
Flashcard(question: " Null Pointer Dereference", answer: "Attacker points to a section of memory where nothing exists, which often causes system to crash"),
Flashcard(question: " Integer Overflow", answer: "Large number is placed into smaller section of memory, forcing extra space to go where memory is overflowed"),
Flashcard(question: " Directory Traversal", answer: "Attackers can read from different parts of a web server, even ones they do not have access to"),
Flashcard(question: " Error messages should show ___ information so that nothing sensitive is shared and they can be reported", answer: "Just Enough"),
Flashcard(question: " All input should be considered ___", answer: "Malicious"),
Flashcard(question: " API (Application Programming Interface)", answer: "Attackers try to manipulate the interface so they can gain additional access or even bring down the system"),
Flashcard(question: " API", answer: "Sends multiple programming interface requests to the server rather than just one"),
Flashcard(question: " DoS", answer: "Can often be done on a single device with no bandwidths"),
Flashcard(question: " DoS", answer: "Attack that uses up available resources on a device so that the application is no longer accessible to others"),
Flashcard(question: " Zip Bomb", answer: "A very small zip file 42kb that when unzipped it expands to 4500 terabytes"),
Flashcard(question: " DHCP Starvation", answer: "Attacker floods network with IP address requests to make it seem like there are many machines on network"),
Flashcard(question: " DCHP starvation makes network ___ to anyone else because all IP addresses have been used", answer: "Unavailable"),
Flashcard(question: " Rogue Access Point", answer: "Access point added to your network without your authorization"),
Flashcard(question: " It is important to use ___ so that are forced to provide authentication before being allowed access to the network", answer: "Network Access Control"),
Flashcard(question: " Wireless Evil Twin", answer: "Designed to look exactly like access points on your network (eg same SSID) but is actually malicious"),
Flashcard(question: " An evil twin, if close enough, can ___ the signal from the other access points and become the main access point", answer: "Overpower"),
Flashcard(question: " ___ are easy to fool with evil twins", answer: "WiFi Hotspots"),
Flashcard(question: " Bluejacking", answer: "An attack that sends unsolicited messages to Bluetooth-enabled devices"),
Flashcard(question: " Since typical Bluetooth range is ___ the attacker would have to be close to send a Bluejacking message", answer: "10 meters"),
Flashcard(question: " Bluesnarfing", answer: "When an attacker can access data on your mobile device using the Bluetooth communications channel"),
Flashcard(question: " Wireless Disassociation Attack", answer: "A DoS attack that is specifically causing devices on the wireless network to not communicate to access point"),
Flashcard(question: " Management Frames", answer: "Your mobile device sends a number of these to the access point, which in turn replies with the same ones"),
Flashcard(question: " Management Frames", answer: "Manage quality of service and association/disassociation with access point"),
Flashcard(question: " ___ did not add protection for management frames, making them vulnerable to attackers", answer: "Original Wireless Standards"),
Flashcard(question: " Sending ___ will disconnect the device from the network", answer: "Deauthentication Frames"),
Flashcard(question: " 802.11w", answer: "Update made in 2014 to protect against deauthorization attacks"),
Flashcard(question: " Certain management frames such as authentication or association need to be ___ in order to connect to device", answer: "Unencrypted"),
Flashcard(question: " 802.11w is required for ___ compliance", answer: "802.11ac"),
Flashcard(question: " Radio Frequency Jamming", answer: "Decrease the signal-to-noise ratio so receiving device can't hear the good signal"),
Flashcard(question: " Signal-to-Noise Ratio", answer: "Makes sure that the signal is louder than the background noise"),
Flashcard(question: " To be able to disrupt devices on local wireless network, the jamming needs to be ___", answer: "Close"),
Flashcard(question: " Fox Hunt", answer: "Directional antenna and headphones, move around to find jamming signal"),
Flashcard(question: " RFID (Radio Frequency Identification)", answer: "Uses radio signals to communicate with a tag placed in or attached to an object, almost anywhere"),
Flashcard(question: " RFID Attacks", answer: "Attacks against radio frequencies including eavesdropping, replay, and DoS"),
Flashcard(question: " NFC (Near Field Communication)", answer: "A form of radio communication that transfers data wirelessly over very short distances (usually 10 cm or less)."),
Flashcard(question: " Cryptography", answer: "Randomizes data so it looks nothing like plain text"),
Flashcard(question: " Without___ an encrypted string of data looks very similar to the original, allowing attackers to reverse engineer it (Puppy example)", answer: "Randomization"),
Flashcard(question: " Electronic Code Book (ECB)", answer: "A process in which plaintext is divided into blocks and each block is then encrypted separately."),
Flashcard(question: " Nonce", answer: "An arbitrary number that can only be used once"),
Flashcard(question: " We often use a cryptographic nonce during the ___ process, then combine it with the hash", answer: "Login"),
Flashcard(question: " Initialization Vector (IV)", answer: "A type of nonce that adds randomization to the encryption method making it stronger"),
Flashcard(question: " Salt", answer: "Makes sure the passwords we are storing are randomized across all users on the system"),
Flashcard(question: " On-Path", answer: "Network attack where someone in the middle can intercept and sometimes change data between two stations"),
Flashcard(question: " In on-path the attacker can ___ or ___ the info before sending it to the intended recipient", answer: "Read Modify"),
Flashcard(question: " ARP Poisoning", answer: "On path attack on local IP subnet, has no security, making it easy for attackers to modify and send"),
Flashcard(question: " Address Resolution Protocol (ARP)", answer: "Message sent to router in the form of router's IP address so that router can send back the MAC address"),
Flashcard(question: " ARP Cache", answer: "Storage for received MAC addresses on computer so it does not have to use ARP every time"),
Flashcard(question: " For an ARP attack to work, the attacker needs to be on the ___", answer: "Local Network"),
Flashcard(question: " In ARP poisoning the attacker sends an ___ ARP message to the device it wants to poison", answer: "Unrequested"),
Flashcard(question: " Once the target has been poisoned, any information will be sent the the MAC address of the ___", answer: "Attacker"),
Flashcard(question: " After poisoning the victim, the attacker then poisons the ___", answer: "Router"),
Flashcard(question: " On-Path Browser Attack", answer: "Malware that is the relay between victim and devices exists on the same computer as the victim"),
Flashcard(question: " For on-path browser attack, an ___ within the malware on the victim's computer is handling the relay", answer: "Automated Process"),
Flashcard(question: " For on-path browser attack, attacker can see victim's data in ___ form before it is sent", answer: "Unencrypted"),
Flashcard(question: " For on path browser attack, malware waits for you to ___ to something such as the bank, then cleans you out", answer: "Login"),
Flashcard(question: " MAC Address", answer: "Physical address of a network adapter, unique to a device"),
Flashcard(question: " In ethernet, MAC address is ___ long and displayed in ___", answer: "48 bits Hexadecimal"),
Flashcard(question: " Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI)", answer: "The first 3 bytes of the MAC address that identifies the manufacturer of the network hardware"),
Flashcard(question: " Serial Number", answer: "The last three bytes of the MAC address, used for every network interface card a company manufactures"),
Flashcard(question: " Switch", answer: "Maintains a list of all the MAC addresses that it knows about on local network so it knows when to receive a particular frame"),
Flashcard(question: " STP (Spanning Tree Protocol)", answer: "Prevent loops in switch"),
Flashcard(question: " If a switch receives an ___ MAC address it will add it and the output interface to the table inside the switch", answer: "Unknown"),
Flashcard(question: " MAC Flooding", answer: "Since switches have limited MAC addresses, attackers can send different ones to the switch to force out the legitimate ones"),
Flashcard(question: " Once MAC flooding is complete, the switch becomes a ___ and transmits all traffic, becoming vulnerable to attackers", answer: "Hub"),
Flashcard(question: " Many switch port ___ can take preventative measures against MAC flooding", answer: "Security Settings"),
Flashcard(question: " MAC Cloning/Spoofing", answer: "Attacker will modify MAC their address to match that of a legitimate device and gain access to a network they shouldn't have"),
Flashcard(question: " In MAC spoofing, communications in victim's MAC will be sent to the ___ instead, causing a DoS for the victim", answer: "Attacker"),
Flashcard(question: " DNS Poisoning", answer: "An attack that substitutes DNS addresses so that the computer is automatically redirected to an attacker's device."),
Flashcard(question: " The ___ takes precedent over any DNS queries", answer: "Host File"),
Flashcard(question: " Once attacker changes DNS IP address, any subsequent users who log into website will be responded to with the ___ IP address", answer: "Incorrect"),
Flashcard(question: " Domain Hijacking", answer: "An attack that changes the registration of a domain name without permission from the owner"),
Flashcard(question: " URL Hijacking", answer: "Redirecting a user to a fictitious website based on a misspelling of the URL. Also called typo squatting."),
Flashcard(question: " Domain Reputation", answer: "Protection for registered domains (email or web server) that provides monitoring and threat intelligence"),
Flashcard(question: " A ___ can be a smokescreen for something like DNS spoofing", answer: "DoS"),
Flashcard(question: " A friendly DoS can be caused by plugging in to the wrong cable and causing a ___ in your network", answer: "Loop"),
Flashcard(question: " Always turn on ___ to prevent layer 2 loops", answer: "STP"),
Flashcard(question: " DDoS", answer: "Large army of computers to bring down a service using something such as bandwidth spikes"),
Flashcard(question: " Attackers often use ___ to perform a DDoS because it consists of thousands of computers", answer: "Botnets"),
Flashcard(question: " Asymmetric Threat", answer: "The attacker may have fewer resources than the victim, so they use more computers to overwhelm the victim"),
Flashcard(question: " DDoS Amplification", answer: "Take a small attack and have it arrive at the victim's machine as a much larger attack"),
Flashcard(question: " For DDoS amplification, the attacker needs to find open ___ and query them with a spoofed IP address", answer: "DNS Resolvers"),
Flashcard(question: " Once responses have grown in the DNS resolvers, they are all then sent to the ___ which can overwhelm it", answer: "Web Server"),
Flashcard(question: " Application DoS", answer: "An attack that causes a service to fail by exploiting a vulnerable application feature e.g. zip bomb"),
Flashcard(question: " Operational Technology DoS", answer: "Shutting down things such as power grids or manufacturing plands"),
Flashcard(question: " Because script is as fast as computer, attacker can have ___ functions find the vulnerable systems", answer: "Many Automated"),
Flashcard(question: " Windows PowerShell", answer: "Extends command line functionality to be able to manage almost every aspect of the operating system"),
Flashcard(question: " Powershell has a ___ function", answer: ".ps1"),
Flashcard(question: " Windows PowerShell uses ___", answer: "cmdlets"),
Flashcard(question: " Python", answer: ".py file extension, popular in many operating systems, and commonly used for cloud orchestration"),
Flashcard(question: " Shell Script", answer: "Used in Unix and Linux, flexible scripting environment, automates and extends command line"),
Flashcard(question: " Since everything in Linux or Unix is done at the ___ the shell script is perfect to automate attacks", answer: "Command Line"),
Flashcard(question: " Macros", answer: "Written specific to certain types of applications to make them easier to use, which can create vulnerabilities"),
Flashcard(question: " VBA (Visual Basic for Applications)", answer: "Programming languages used to implement macros and scripting in Office document automation"),
Flashcard(question: " Attackers can target the ___ since VBA is connected to it", answer: "Operating System"),
Flashcard(question: " Threat Actor", answer: "An entity responsible for an event that has an impact on the safety of another entity"),
Flashcard(question: " APT (Advanced Persistent Threat)", answer: "A threat that is able to get into your network and stays there until you take it out"),
Flashcard(question: " An APT takes ___ days to be detected in North and South America and even longer in other places", answer: "71"),
Flashcard(question: " Insiders", answer: "Employers or contractors who work for organization, usually know things such as data center location"),
Flashcard(question: " Nation State", answer: "Usually with the government and in charge of national security, always external and many resources"),
Flashcard(question: " Hacktivist", answer: "Hacker with a purpose or goal against a third party, usually social change or political agenda"),
Flashcard(question: " Hacktivists are very focused on a ___", answer: "Single Message"),
Flashcard(question: " Script Kiddie", answer: "Focused on running very simple scripts to be able to gain access to someone's network"),
Flashcard(question: " Script kiddies throw ___ different scripts at a network hoping one of them will go in", answer: "Many"),
Flashcard(question: " Script kiddies are motivated by ___ (Hey I gained access to someone's network!)", answer: "Bragging Rights"),
Flashcard(question: " Organized Crime", answer: "A set of professional criminals motivated by money, very sophisticated and always external"),
Flashcard(question: " Shadow IT", answer: "You are performing your own IT functions without working with your internal IT department"),
Flashcard(question: " Shadow IT operators use their own equipment or procedures because they feel that the procedures of their company's IT department put up ___ to do their job", answer: "Roadblocks"),
Flashcard(question: " Competitors", answer: "Companies who want to take down a company through computer attacks and unethical means (eg. steal customer lists)"),
Flashcard(question: " Attack Vector", answer: "Method used by an attacker to gain access to a victim's network"),
Flashcard(question: " Direct Access Attack Vector", answer: "Physical access to a system; the reason we lock up data centers, (eg. transfer data onto flash drive)"),
Flashcard(question: " A form of direct access attack vector is to attach a ___ to a keyboard and see what everyone typed on it", answer: "Keylogger"),
Flashcard(question: " Wireless Attack Vectors", answer: "Wireless access to the system such as rogue access points or evil twins"),
Flashcard(question: " Email Attack Vectors", answer: "One of the largest and most successful attack vectors, easy to phish or attach malware"),
Flashcard(question: " Supply Chain Attack Vectors", answer: "Hackers try to compromise target by exploiting vulnerabilities in a third party vector"),
Flashcard(question: " Social Media Attack Vectors", answer: "Looking at social media account to gather information"),
Flashcard(question: " Removable Media Attack Vectors", answer: "Using something such as a USB drive to inject malicious software or gather files"),
Flashcard(question: " Cloud Attack Vectors", answer: "Viruses, email attachments, pop ups, or anything that can get data in the cloud"),
Flashcard(question: " Threat Intelligence", answer: "The process of investigating and collecting information about emerging threats and threat sources"),
Flashcard(question: " Open-Source Intelligence (OSINT)", answer: "Information that is readily available to the public and doesn't require any type of malicious activity to obtain"),
Flashcard(question: " Closed/Proprietary Intelligence", answer: "Compiled threat information that people are in business to make available to you for a cost"),
Flashcard(question: " Vulnerability Databases", answer: "Large databases that compile information coming from many different researchers"),
Flashcard(question: " Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE)", answer: "An online list of known vulnerabilities (and patches) to software, especially web servers. Sponsored by DHS and CISA"),
Flashcard(question: " U.S. National Vulnerability Database (NVD)", answer: "Summary of CVEs that you can browse to find vulnerabilities that may affect you"),
Flashcard(question: " ___ databases sometimes provide info that is classified but made available by the federal government", answer: "Public Threat Intelligence"),
Flashcard(question: " Private Threat Intelligence", answer: "Companies that share information especially organizations in the IT security industry"),
Flashcard(question: " CTA (Cyber Threat Intelligence)", answer: "Members upload the information they have about a particular threat, and it is evaluated and uploaded to the organization"),
Flashcard(question: " Automated Indicator Sharing (AIS)", answer: "Enables the exchange of cyber threat indicators, at machine speed, among the Federal Government"),
Flashcard(question: " STIX (Structured Threat Information eXpression)", answer: "Describes cyber threat information and includes motivation, capabilities, etc"),
Flashcard(question: " TAXII (Trusted Automated eXchange of Indicator Information)", answer: "Safely transfer the STIX data between organizations"),
Flashcard(question: " Dark Web", answer: "Overlay to existing internet that requires specialized software to be able to access"),
Flashcard(question: " The ___ can be used to find the activities and transactions of hacking groups and services", answer: "Dark Web"),
Flashcard(question: " IOC (Indicator of Compromise)", answer: "A sign that an asset or network has been attacked or is currently under attack"),
Flashcard(question: " Indicators of compromise include ___ amount of internet activity or ___ file hash values", answer: "Unusual Changed"),
Flashcard(question: " Predicative Analysis", answer: "Analyze very large amounts of data very quickly and find suspicious patterns"),
Flashcard(question: " Threat Maps", answer: "A real-time map of the computer security attacks that are going on at any given time"),
Flashcard(question: " File/Code Repositories", answer: "See what hackers are using to build their attacks, GitHub, private code can often be released public which is then used by hackers"),
Flashcard(question: " Threat Research", answer: "A never ending process; have to know your enemy and their tools of war"),
Flashcard(question: " Vendor Websites", answer: "The ones who wrote the software and know when problems are announced"),
Flashcard(question: " National Vulnerability Database (NVD)", answer: "The U.S. government repository of standards-based vulnerability management data"),
Flashcard(question: " It is common to supplement the NVD with ___ feeds from other organizations", answer: "Third Party"),
Flashcard(question: " Conferences", answer: "An in-person way to learn the latest of vulnerabilities and threats, usually from researchers"),
Flashcard(question: " Academic Journals", answer: "Research from professionals with cutting edge security analysis"),
Flashcard(question: " Request for Comments (RFC)", answer: "Documents are how standards and protocols are defined and published for all to see"),
Flashcard(question: " Local Industry Groups", answer: "Usually associations, a gathering of local peers to discuss local cybersecurity challenges"),
Flashcard(question: " Threat Feeds", answer: "Cybersecurity data feeds that provide information on the latest and most dangerous threats"),
Flashcard(question: " TTP (Tactics, Techniques, and Procedures)", answer: "Analysis of historical cyber-attacks and adversary actions and how they perform them"),
Flashcard(question: " Zero-Day Attacks", answer: "Attacks that exploit previously unknown vulnerabilities, so victims have no time to prepare or defend against the attacks"),
Flashcard(question: " Open Permissions", answer: "Information has been put onto the internet but no security has been applied to that data, easy for hackers to access"),
Flashcard(question: " Open permissions have become increasingly common with ___", answer: "Cloud Storage"),
Flashcard(question: " Unsecured Root Accounts", answer: "Unprotected accounts that give unfettered access to all resources, even worse if admin account"),
Flashcard(question: " Sometimes you can put too much information in an ___ message, and this info can be used against us", answer: "Error"),
Flashcard(question: " Weak Encryption", answer: "Encryption that is relatively easy or simple to decrypt without the encryption key, type of vulnerability"),
Flashcard(question: " TLS (Transport Layer Security)", answer: "We commonly use this protocol in our browsers to encrypt data, one of the most common vulnerability issues"),
Flashcard(question: " There are over ___ cipher suites in TLS", answer: "300"),
Flashcard(question: " Insecure Protocols", answer: "Some protocols aren't encrypted; all traffic sent in the clear ex. Telnet, FTP, SMTP, IMAP"),
Flashcard(question: " If you are not sure an application is sending information in the clear you can verify with a ___", answer: "Packet Capture"),
Flashcard(question: " If a packet capture is read in ___ then it is not being encrypted during transport", answer: "Plain English"),
Flashcard(question: " Encrypted Protocols", answer: "SSH, SFTP, IMAPS, etc. better than insecure protocols"),
Flashcard(question: " Wall of Sheep", answer: "A list of everybody communicating on the network in the clear along with the passwords"),
Flashcard(question: " Attackers know that some users don't change their ___ making them vulnerable", answer: "Default Settings"),
Flashcard(question: " Mirai Botnet", answer: "Takes advantage of default usernames and passwords to gain access to systems and take over for their own use"),
Flashcard(question: " To make things worse, the Mirai Botnet is now ___ so hackers can download and modify it for their own means", answer: "Open Source"),
Flashcard(question: " You have to ___ on the server so applications can talk to the server itself", answer: "Open Ports"),
Flashcard(question: " We often manage traffic flows with ___ which can allow or deny based on port number or application", answer: "Firewalls"),
Flashcard(question: " Improper Patch Management", answer: "Often centrally managed, can be very damaging if not up to date"),
Flashcard(question: " Legacy Platforms", answer: "Used to describe systems that are no longer being marketed or supported, can be a security concern"),
Flashcard(question: " IT security does not change because it is a ___", answer: "Third Party"),
Flashcard(question: " System Integration Risk", answer: "People who install systems have either virtual access to a system or physical (keyloggers, etc.)"),
Flashcard(question: " System integrators are a risk because they have access to the ___ without having to go through security protocols", answer: "Internal Network"),
Flashcard(question: " ___ are the only ones who can fix their products, so it is important to have vendor support", answer: "Vendors"),
Flashcard(question: " You can't always control security at a ___ location, which puts supply chains at risk", answer: "Third Party"),
Flashcard(question: " Outsourced Code Development", answer: "Contracting with third parties to assist the organization in the development and writing of a software program"),
Flashcard(question: " If data is stored at a third party encryption, we need to make sure all communications in and out are over an ___", answer: "Encrypted Channel"),
Flashcard(question: " In some cases losing ___ can be more damaging than losing money", answer: "Data"),
Flashcard(question: " Meow Attack", answer: "This attack overwrote data and wrote it with this word"),
Flashcard(question: " Identity Theft", answer: "A crime that involves someone pretending to be another person in order to steal money or obtain benefits"),
Flashcard(question: " Security breaches can result in heavy ___ of millions of dollars", answer: "Financial Loss"),
Flashcard(question: " Getting hacked impacts the ___ of an organization, resulting in stock drops and disclosures", answer: "Reputation"),
Flashcard(question: " The problem with intelligence data is that it is ___ so we can't respond until the attack occurs", answer: "Reactive"),
Flashcard(question: " Intelligence Fusion", answer: "Putting all the data into a massive database so you can pick out the most important pieces of data"),
Flashcard(question: " Fusing Data", answer: "Involves collecting intelligence, using outside sources, then analyzing big data"),
Flashcard(question: " Vulnerability Scanning", answer: "The act of scanning for weaknesses and susceptibilities in the network and on individual systems"),
Flashcard(question: " Port Scan", answer: "Sees which ports are open on a particular IP address to see what might not be secure"),
Flashcard(question: " You want to perform vulnerability scans from the perspective of the ___ (outside and inside)", answer: "Attacker"),
Flashcard(question: " Non-Intrusive Scans", answer: "Gather information, don't try to exploit a vulnerability"),
Flashcard(question: " Intrusive Scans", answer: "You'll try out the vulnerability to see if it works"),
Flashcard(question: " Non-Credentialed Scans", answer: "Run from the perspective of someone who does not have access to the remote device"),
Flashcard(question: " Credentialed Scan", answer: "Run under context of a valid account and are typically more accurate than non-credentialed scans"),
Flashcard(question: " Make sure ___ knows what's happening because a vulnerability scan could potentially crash the device", answer: "Everyone"),
Flashcard(question: " Application Scan", answer: "An automated test used to identify weaknesses in a software application like desktop"),
Flashcard(question: " Web Application Scan", answer: "Scans software on a web server for vulnerabilities"),
Flashcard(question: " CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System)", answer: "Provides scoring of vulnerabilities on a scale of 1-10 so you can determine which ones are the most severe"),
Flashcard(question: " False Positive", answer: "A vulnerability is identified that doesn't really exist"),
Flashcard(question: " False Negative", answer: "A vulnerability that exists but was not detected"),
Flashcard(question: " Configuration Review", answer: "To verify the operating condition and the effectiveness of its security configuration and rule sets"),
Flashcard(question: " SIEM (Security Information and Event Management)", answer: "Logging of security events and information onto the central database"),
Flashcard(question: " Syslog", answer: "Sends system status messages from several different devices to a central server for monitoring and review"),
Flashcard(question: " Syslog needs a ___ of space since it is collecting data from many different devices", answer: "Large Amount"),
Flashcard(question: " Data Inputs", answer: "Server authentication attempts, VPN connections, firewall session logs etc. that should be in SIEM"),
Flashcard(question: " ___ are a common part of SIEM data", answer: "Packet Captures"),
Flashcard(question: " SOC (Security Operations Center)", answer: "The location where security professionals monitor and protect critical information assets in an organization, can monitor SIEM data"),
Flashcard(question: " There is a constant ___ in a SIEM", answer: "Information Flow"),
Flashcard(question: " SIEMs have a ___ that rolls up information into a mode that can be easily identified", answer: "Dashboard"),
Flashcard(question: " Big Data Analytics", answer: "The ability to look through large amounts of very diverse data and identify patterns normally invisible to a human being"),
Flashcard(question: " UEBA (User and Entity Behavior Analytics)", answer: "A system that can provide automated identification of suspicious activity by user accounts and computer hosts"),
Flashcard(question: " Sentiment Analysis", answer: "Examines how public views a particular organization; if public opinion is bad, it tends to attract hackers"),
Flashcard(question: " SOAR (Security Orchestration, Automation, and Response)", answer: "Takes manual and tedious security processes and automates them so they can be done at computer speed"),
Flashcard(question: " Orchestration", answer: "Using many tools together such as firewalls, account management, and email filters"),
Flashcard(question: " Penetration Test", answer: "An authorized attempt to break into the organization's information system by exploiting vulnerabilities"),
Flashcard(question: " Rules of Engagement", answer: "Penetration test document that defines purpose and makes everyone aware of parameters"),
Flashcard(question: " The rules of engagement also lists the ___ of the devices that are in scope for the penetration test", answer: "IP Addresses"),
Flashcard(question: " Blind Test", answer: "Pentester knows nothing about the systems they are testing on"),
Flashcard(question: " Known Environment", answer: "In a penetration test where tester knows everything about device"),
Flashcard(question: " Partially Known Environment", answer: "Mix of known and unknown, may be contracting with third party who runs pentests on key systems"),
Flashcard(question: " It is important that the person performing the penetration test has permission to ___ on that system", answer: "Exploit Vulnerabilities"),
Flashcard(question: " A good penetration tests tries many different ___", answer: "Vulnerability Types"),
Flashcard(question: " Lateral Movement", answer: "Moving from device to device within a network during penetration test"),
Flashcard(question: " It's very common to have stronger security on the ___ of the network", answer: "Perimeter"),
Flashcard(question: " Persistence", answer: "Making sure there is a way back into the account after the penetration test is done"),
Flashcard(question: " Pivot Point", answer: "Gaining access to a system and using that system to get to any other system on the network"),
Flashcard(question: " After penetration test, all systems need to be ___ to how they were before the test", answer: "Reverted Back"),
Flashcard(question: " Bug Bounty", answer: "Reward scheme operated by software and web services vendors for reporting vulnerabilities"),
Flashcard(question: " Reconaissance", answer: "Footprinting all of the devices in an organization to understand its security measures"),
Flashcard(question: " Network Map", answer: "Part of recon, used to identify routers, networks, and remote sites"),
Flashcard(question: " Passive Footprinting", answer: "Gathering information about a target without direct interaction using open sources (eg. social media)"),
Flashcard(question: " OSINT (Open Source Intelligence)", answer: "Find information on anyone or anything, not related to OSS"),
Flashcard(question: " Wardriving of Warflying", answer: "Combining WiFi analysis with GPS locations to know where a wireless network might be, using car or drone"),
Flashcard(question: " Active Footprinting", answer: "Effort is one that requires the attacker to touch the device, network, or resource (eg. ping and port scans)"),
Flashcard(question: " In cybersecurity, analysts become an expert in their ___", answer: "Niche"),
Flashcard(question: " Red Team", answer: "The offense team, usually hired attackers or ethical hackers"),
Flashcard(question: " Blue Team", answer: "The defense team that protects the data, day-to-day operational security"),
Flashcard(question: " Purple Team", answer: "Red and blue teams working together so they can share information instead of compete"),
Flashcard(question: " White Team", answer: "Manages interactions between red and blue teams, enforces rules, basically refs"),
Flashcard(question: " The only constant with cybersecurity is ___", answer: "Change"),
Flashcard(question: " Configuration Management", answer: "The process of ensuring that only authorized changes are made to a system and they are modified and documented"),
Flashcard(question: " Network Diagram", answer: "Map of which devices are connected to each other, sometimes diagram of what racks they are in"),
Flashcard(question: " In a data center, equipment can be spread across many different racks but are still ___ via wires under the floor", answer: "Connected"),
Flashcard(question: " Baseline Configuration", answer: "Security of an application environment must be well defined and all app instances will follow it"),
Flashcard(question: " Integrity Measurements Check", answer: "Checks to see if all details in your documentation match what is running in that particular application"),
Flashcard(question: " For configuration management, create a ___ that is easily understood by everyone so they can better complete tasks", answer: "Standard"),
Flashcard(question: " IP Schema", answer: "A way of knowing which IP addresses are used at which locations to avoid confusion"),
Flashcard(question: " Protecting Data", answer: "A primary job task in cybersecurity"),
Flashcard(question: " Data Sovereignty", answer: "The laws associated with data depending on where it resides; laws may prohibit where it is stored"),
Flashcard(question: " Data Obfuscation", answer: "Data transformation that makes it difficult for a human to recognize the original data, such as x's on receipts"),
Flashcard(question: " Data Encryption", answer: "The process of making data from plaintext to ciphertext to make it unreadable"),
Flashcard(question: " If you have the ___ you can convert ciphertext to plaintext and vice-versa", answer: "Proper Key"),
Flashcard(question: " Confusion", answer: "The info we are encrypting and putting into ciphertext is very different than original info in plaintext"),
Flashcard(question: " Diffusion", answer: "If you change one piece of info in the plaintext, the resulting cipher text will be dramatically different"),
Flashcard(question: " Data-At-Rest", answer: "Data that is stored on a storage device, needs to be encrypted to be protected"),
Flashcard(question: " Data-In-Transmit", answer: "Data going between switches, routers, and devices, not as much protection because it is travelling"),
Flashcard(question: " Data-In-Use", answer: "Data actively processing in the memory, such as RAM, GPU registers, and cache"),
Flashcard(question: " Data-in-use is almost always ___ making it a preferred place for attackers", answer: "Decrypted"),
Flashcard(question: " Tokenization", answer: "Replacing sensitive data with a completely different set of data"),
Flashcard(question: " IRM (Information Rights Management)", answer: "Restricts data from unauthorized persons, (eg. PDF that won't allow you to copy and paste)"),
Flashcard(question: " DLP (Data Loss Prevention)", answer: "Looks in several different locations and protects data from prying eyes"),
Flashcard(question: " Endpoint DLP Solution", answer: "Resides on our local workstations and devices; examines everything being transferred in and out of device"),
Flashcard(question: " DLP on a workstation can allow or disallow access to data that's being stored on a ___", answer: "USB Drive"),
Flashcard(question: " Cloud-Based DLP", answer: "Able to look for all traffic going through the cloud to see if predefined data strings exist within data flows"),
Flashcard(question: " We need DLP on our ___ to block any information classified as sensitive", answer: "Email Systems"),
Flashcard(question: " Offsite Backup", answer: "Organization-owned site or third party facility"),
Flashcard(question: " Offsite Recovery", answer: "Sending critical data off the main site as a disaster plan"),
Flashcard(question: " An incidence response plan consists of ___ to help us know how to identify and respond to an attack", answer: "Documented Processes"),
Flashcard(question: " SSL/TLS Inspection", answer: "Commonly used to view information within incoming and outgoing encrypted SSL/TLS packets"),
Flashcard(question: " SSL/TLS inspection relies on ___", answer: "Trust"),
Flashcard(question: " The trust of SSL comes from a list of ___ embedded within the browser of your device", answer: "CAs"),
Flashcard(question: " Your browser does not trust a website unless a ___ has signed the web server's encryption certificate", answer: "CA"),
Flashcard(question: " SSL/TLS Proxy", answer: "Inserted in the middle of the conversation and can decrypt the data flow to check for malicious content"),
Flashcard(question: " Hashing can also be a ___", answer: "Digital Signature"),
Flashcard(question: " To protect API you should ___ the login page", answer: "Secure"),
Flashcard(question: " On-Path Attack", answer: "Intercept and modify API messages, replay API commands"),
Flashcard(question: " API Injection", answer: "Get into middle of conversation, see how API operates, then put own data into API flows"),
Flashcard(question: " Authentication", answer: "Limit API access to legitimate users over secure protocols"),
Flashcard(question: " Authorization", answer: "API should not allow extended access, each user has a limited role"),
Flashcard(question: " WAF (Web Application Firewall)", answer: "Can apply rules to API communication"),
Flashcard(question: " When disaster happens you need to move everything to an ___ site", answer: "Alternate"),
Flashcard(question: " You need processes and procedures for moving to the recovery site, and also for moving back to the ___", answer: "Original Location"),
Flashcard(question: " Hot Site", answer: "An exact replica of what we are running in our production environment"),
Flashcard(question: " Because the recovery and main sites are a ___ it is easy to flip the switch to move the data between each", answer: "Mirror Image"),
Flashcard(question: " Cold Site", answer: "No hardware, empty building which means you need to bring the data with you"),
Flashcard(question: " Warm Site", answer: "Big room with rack space so you can set up the hardware in a short amount of time"),
Flashcard(question: " Honeypot", answer: "A system designed to look very attractive so that attackers fall for it and get trapped"),
Flashcard(question: " With honeypots the attacker is probably a ___", answer: "Machine"),
Flashcard(question: " The honeypot needs to look and feel like a ___ so that the attacker does not know it is a honeypot", answer: "Real System"),
Flashcard(question: " Honeynet", answer: "Multiple honeypots where you can begin gathering information from multiple sources"),
Flashcard(question: " Honeyfile", answer: "Bait within the honeypot that you hope the attacker will go after"),
Flashcard(question: " ___ can take big data and identify patterns and info within that large data source", answer: "Machine Learning"),
Flashcard(question: " Machine learning needs to be fed with ___ (malware, viruses, etc.) so it knows what to look for", answer: "Actual Data"),
Flashcard(question: " Fake Telemetry", answer: "Inserted into data to get a machine to think that the malware is actually good"),
Flashcard(question: " DNS Sinkhole", answer: "A DNS server that gives out incorrect info about the IP address of a particular FQDN"),
Flashcard(question: " FQDN (Fully Qualified Domain Name)", answer: "A host name plus domain name that uniquely identifies a computer or location on a network"),
Flashcard(question: " IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service)", answer: "Cloud-hosted provider of virtualized servers and networks, eg. web server"),
Flashcard(question: " SaaS (Software as a Service)", answer: "Pay for software as you use it. Not installed locally, instead it is hosted software e.g. Google Docs"),
Flashcard(question: " PaaS (Platform as a Service)", answer: "Cloud-based virtual server(s). These virtualized platforms give programmers tools needed to deploy, administer, and maintain a Web application."),
Flashcard(question: " XaaS (Anything as a Service)", answer: "A broad description of any type of service provided over the cloud"),
Flashcard(question: " On Premises", answer: "Cloud model where all technology needed to run an application would be on systems in your premises"),
Flashcard(question: " MSP (Managed Service Provider)", answer: "Provides network connectivity, disaster recovery, etc to make sure your systems are to scale"),
Flashcard(question: " MSSP (Managed Security Service Provider)", answer: "Focuses on IT security such as firewall or patch management"),
Flashcard(question: " Off Premises", answer: "Servers are located in the building of a third party"),
Flashcard(question: " Public", answer: "Cloud service available to anyone"),
Flashcard(question: " Community", answer: "Several organizations pool resources together to create a shared set of cloud services"),
Flashcard(question: " Private", answer: "Cloud service internal in your data center that only you have access to"),
Flashcard(question: " Hybrid", answer: "Cloud service that has both public and private cloud models"),
Flashcard(question: " Since the cloud is ___ it is difficult to protect data", answer: "Far"),
Flashcard(question: " IoT (Internet of Things)", answer: "A computing concept that describes where everyday physical objects are connected to the Internet"),
Flashcard(question: " Edge Computing", answer: "Applications that are running and their data all occur on local system and don't have to connect to internet"),
Flashcard(question: " Fog Computing", answer: "Allows us to send some data into the cloud for processing without requiring all the data be in one place"),
Flashcard(question: " Thin Client", answer: "Single device that allows us to connect keyboard, mouse, and monitor and then connect to desktop running in cloud"),
Flashcard(question: " Virtualization", answer: "Running multiple operating systems on a single physical piece of hardware"),
Flashcard(question: " Hypervisor", answer: "Manages all the different operating systems running on a computer"),
Flashcard(question: " Containerization", answer: "Run multiple applications in the same sandbox, but not have separate host operating systems for each one"),
Flashcard(question: " Monolithic", answer: "A single application that contains all the decision making processes and does everything"),
Flashcard(question: " API (Application Programming Interface)", answer: "Breaks up an application into individual services"),
Flashcard(question: " Microservice", answer: "A small reusable chunk of code that performs a specific function that is a part of a larger application"),
Flashcard(question: " Serverless Architecture", answer: "Applications are separated into autonomous functions; remove operating system from the equation"),
Flashcard(question: " Stateless Compute Container", answer: "Processors designed to respond to API requests; used for serverless architecture"),
Flashcard(question: " VPC (Virtual Private Cloud)", answer: "A pool of resources created in a public cloud"),
Flashcard(question: " Transit Gateway", answer: "Connect thousands of VPC and on-premises networks together"),
Flashcard(question: " Resource Policies", answer: "Assigning permissions to cloud resources, can be difficult since the cloud is always running"),
Flashcard(question: " SIAM (Service Integration and Management)", answer: "Consolidates all the different cloud services into one single management interface"),
Flashcard(question: " Infrastructure as Code", answer: "Defines servers, network, and applications as a series of code"),
Flashcard(question: " Infrastructure as a code is an important concept for ___", answer: "Cloud Computing"),
Flashcard(question: " SDN (Software Defined Networking)", answer: "Separating functionality of networking devices into two functional planes of operation (control and data)"),
Flashcard(question: " Control Plane", answer: "Handles management and ongoing configuration of the device"),
Flashcard(question: " Data Plane", answer: "Part of device that handles the actual operation"),
Flashcard(question: " SDN devices are ___ managed", answer: "Centrally"),
Flashcard(question: " SDN follows a set of ___", answer: "Open Standards"),
Flashcard(question: " SDV (Software Defined Visibility)", answer: "Allows us to deploy firewalls and security devices while understanding what type of data is flowing between systems"),
Flashcard(question: " Virtual Machine Sprawl", answer: "The widespread proliferation of virtual machines without proper oversight or management"),
Flashcard(question: " Everything happening on a virtual machine happens within because it is ___", answer: "Self-Contained"),
Flashcard(question: " Virtual Machine Escape", answer: "When a user (or malware) is able to break out of a VM's isolation (or lack thereof) and gain access to the hosting computer"),
Flashcard(question: " Sandbox", answer: "Isolated testing environment that can be used by developers to test aspects of app they are developing"),
Flashcard(question: " Developer", answer: "Writes code and tests aspects of its functionality"),
Flashcard(question: " Quality Assurance", answer: "People who verify application features are working and can also test new features"),
Flashcard(question: " Staging", answer: "Application is tested in a real world environment"),
Flashcard(question: " Security Baseline", answer: "Something all application instances must follow, usually needs frequent updates"),
Flashcard(question: " Integrity Check", answer: "Makes sure the app's production environment matches requirements on original security baseline"),
Flashcard(question: " Provisioning", answer: "The process of deploying servers and making them available"),
Flashcard(question: " Scalability", answer: "How well a system can scale up, or adapt to the increased demands of growth"),
Flashcard(question: " Elasticity", answer: "The ability to increase or decrease available resources for an application based on workload"),
Flashcard(question: " Orchestration", answer: "The key to cloud computing, automates provisioning and deprovisioning of applications"),
Flashcard(question: " Deprovisioning", answer: "Completely removing any remnants of an app from running in your environment"),
Flashcard(question: " Stored Procedures", answer: "A group of SQL statements that execute as a whole, similar to a mini-program. Developers use them to prevent SQL injection attacks"),
Flashcard(question: " Stored procedures are stored on the ___ itself", answer: "Database Server"),
Flashcard(question: " Obfuscation", answer: "Make something normally understandable difficult to understand"),
Flashcard(question: " Code Reuse", answer: "Common for developers, use old code to make new applications"),
Flashcard(question: " If the old code has security vulnerabilities, reusing it can spread them to ___", answer: "Multiple Applications"),
Flashcard(question: " Dead Code", answer: "Put into the application, processing logic but the results of that logic aren't used anywhere else on the app"),
Flashcard(question: " Input Validation", answer: "A programming process that verifies data is valid before using it"),
Flashcard(question: " Normalization", answer: "Check and correct all input into an application"),
Flashcard(question: " Server-Side Validation", answer: "Code on the server looks through data to make sure the input has been done correctly"),
Flashcard(question: " Client-Side Validation", answer: "The end-user application will verify the input on the client's machine before sending to the server"),
Flashcard(question: " Server-side validation is considered ___ than client-side", answer: "Safer"),
Flashcard(question: " Buffer Overflow", answer: "A technique for crashing by sending too much data to a section of the computer's memory"),
Flashcard(question: " SDK (software development kit)", answer: "Written by someone else, extends functionality of programming language"),
Flashcard(question: " Version Control", answer: "A process to keep track of what changes were made to what files so that a specific version can be referred to and improvements in multiple versions can be merged together."),
Flashcard(question: " Software Diversity", answer: "People might all run the OS or app the same but each person has a unique final binary file"),
Flashcard(question: " Continuous Integration", answer: "App is constantly updated and code is merged into central repository several times a day"),
Flashcard(question: " Continuous Delivery", answer: "Automate the testing and release of security application, then wait for us to click a button to deploy"),
Flashcard(question: " Continuous Deployment", answer: "Entire testing, release and deployment process of an app is automated"),
Flashcard(question: " Directory Services", answer: "Central database that stores usernames, passwords, computers, devices connected to network"),
Flashcard(question: " Directory service database is distributed across ___ that all communicate with each other", answer: "Multiple Services"),
Flashcard(question: " Directory services require a ___", answer: "Single Authentication"),
Flashcard(question: " Federation", answer: "A way to allow someone to authenticate to your network using credentials stored with a third party (eg. log in with facebook)"),
Flashcard(question: " Attestation", answer: "Have the system prove that hardware connecting into your network is actually yours"),
Flashcard(question: " Remote Attestation", answer: "Remote system verifies files are the same and makes sure that the system is safe"),
Flashcard(question: " SMS (Short Message Service)", answer: "Short text messages, typically fewer than 300 characters"),
Flashcard(question: " Push Notification", answer: "Allows an application to notify a user of new messages or events, even when the user is not actively using the app"),
Flashcard(question: " A ___ token generator provides coding and is a useful authentication factor", answer: "Pseudo-Random"),
Flashcard(question: " TOTP (Time-Based One-Time Password)", answer: "Pseudo random number will be available as a login credential for usually about 30 seconds before changing"),
Flashcard(question: " HOTP (HMAC-based one-time password)", answer: "For authentication, you have a number you would use once then never use again"),
Flashcard(question: " You can also use a ___ to have someone tell you an authentication code", answer: "Phone Call"),
Flashcard(question: " Static Codes", answer: "codes that do not change over time such as a PIN"),
Flashcard(question: " Gait Analysis", answer: "A biometric factor that identifies someone based on how they walk"),
Flashcard(question: " Vascular Scanner", answer: "Biometric factor that identifies people based on layout of their veins"),
Flashcard(question: " FAR (False Acceptance Rate)", answer: "How often an unauthorized user will be approved by biometrics"),
Flashcard(question: " FRR (False Rejection Rate)", answer: "How often authorized users are rejected by the system, usually because it is too sensitive"),
Flashcard(question: " CER (Crossover Error Rate)", answer: "The rate where false rejection rate and the false acceptance rate are equal, usually by dialing both down"),
Flashcard(question: " AAA Framework", answer: "Authentication, Authorization, and Accounting"),
Flashcard(question: " A ___ authentication involves a centralized platform managed by a third party", answer: "Cloud-Based"),
Flashcard(question: " An ___ authentication system is on a local data center with internal monitoring and management", answer: "On-Premises"),
Flashcard(question: " Authentication Factor", answer: "Comparing a characteristic to what you know is associated with an individual"),
Flashcard(question: " Authentication Attribute", answer: "May not be directly associated with individual, but can include with other authentication factors to prove someone's identity"),
Flashcard(question: " Multi factor authentication uses something you ___, ____ and ___", answer: "Know Have Are"),
Flashcard(question: " Somewhere You Are", answer: "An authentication factor indicating location, often using geolocation technologies"),
Flashcard(question: " Something You Can Do", answer: "Authentication based on how you do things such as a signature"),
Flashcard(question: " Something You Exhibit", answer: "Authentication factor based on unique trait such as how you type of walk"),
Flashcard(question: " Redundancy", answer: "How we duplicate parts of a system so that it is always up and running"),
Flashcard(question: " Geographic Dispersal", answer: "Moving technologies to several different areas in case a disaster happens in the local area"),
Flashcard(question: " Multipath Input/Output", answer: "Allows us to create other routes on the network that we can use to work around problems we might have"),
Flashcard(question: " RAID (Redundant Array of Independent Disks)", answer: "Using multiple drives within a single array, so if you lose data on one you can pull data from the others"),
Flashcard(question: " RAID 1 (Mirroring)", answer: "Two drives are used in unison, and all data is written to both drives, giving you an extra copy of the data, in the case that one drive fails"),
Flashcard(question: " RAID 5 (Striping With Parity)", answer: "Putting pieces of info on separate physical drives and putting some equivalent info on a final physical drive"),
Flashcard(question: " Load Balancer", answer: "Balances inbound and outbound connections to applications or service endpoints by choosing which servers to use"),
Flashcard(question: " NIC Teaming", answer: "Allows us to use primary and standby connections in a server simultaneously and aggregate bandwidth between them"),
Flashcard(question: " NICs talk to each other over a ___ connection", answer: "Multicast"),
Flashcard(question: " Port Aggregation", answer: "Joining multiple network device ports together for increased bandwidth and redundancy"),
Flashcard(question: " UPS (Uninterruptible Power Supply)", answer: "A device that provides backup power when the electrical power fails or drops to an unacceptable voltage level"),
Flashcard(question: " Offline/Standby", answer: "A UPS that is not normally enabled unless power is lost"),
Flashcard(question: " Line-Interactive", answer: "A UPS where if power is slowly diminishing it can slowly ramp up the power provided by the batteries"),
Flashcard(question: " Online/Double Conversion", answer: "UPS that always provides power and has no switching process when power goes out"),
Flashcard(question: " Generator", answer: "Long term power backup that can keep power running for days or weeks, uses fuel"),
Flashcard(question: " Power Redundancy", answer: "Having backup power sources in case the primary one fails"),
Flashcard(question: " If there are plugs in power sources on both sides of the power unit, then each source provides ___ of the power", answer: "0.5"),
Flashcard(question: " Hot Swappable", answer: "The feature of a component that allows it to be installed or removed without disrupting operations"),
Flashcard(question: " PDU (Power Distribution Unit)", answer: "Provides multiple power sources, such as a strip with multiple plug outlets"),
Flashcard(question: " SAN (Storage Area Network)", answer: "A specialized network of high-speed storage devices with built-in redundancy"),
Flashcard(question: " SAN Snapshot", answer: "Take data from one SAN, take exact makeup of data, and copy that data to a separate SAN"),
Flashcard(question: " VM Replication", answer: "Update one virtual machine and copy that update to all the other virtual machines"),
Flashcard(question: " Archive Attribute", answer: "Set when a file is modified, can access advanced options for a file"),
Flashcard(question: " Full Backup", answer: "Take everything in the operating system and save it"),
Flashcard(question: " Incremental Backup", answer: "Occurs after full backup, will back up all files that have changed since the last one"),
Flashcard(question: " Differential Backup", answer: "Occurs after full backup, but only files that are backed up are ones that have changed since last full backup"),
Flashcard(question: " For full restoration, you need every ___ and ___ backup that has occurred", answer: "Full Incremental"),
Flashcard(question: " Magnetic Tape", answer: "Sequential storage and can be from 100GB to several TB in storage"),
Flashcard(question: " Disk", answer: "Faster than tapes and can duplicate and compress data"),
Flashcard(question: " Copy", answer: "An exact duplicate of a system at a particular point in time"),
Flashcard(question: " NAS (Network Attached Storage)", answer: "Provides access to large storage array that's connected over the network"),
Flashcard(question: " A NAS is ___ meaning if you have to change any portion of a file on it, you have to rewrite the entire file", answer: "File-Level Access"),
Flashcard(question: " SAN (Storage Area Network)", answer: "Configured to look like a separate storage drive on your system, efficient reading and writing"),
Flashcard(question: " A SAN provides ___ so if you need to change a single portion of a large file, you only need to change that portion on the disk", answer: "Block-Level Access"),
Flashcard(question: " Image Backup", answer: "Backup everything on a computer and create an exact replica of the entire file system"),
Flashcard(question: " Offline Backup", answer: "Backing up to local devices on a fast and secure channel"),
Flashcard(question: " Online Backup", answer: "Constantly accessible, usually to a third party or cloud-based service, like cloud storage"),
Flashcard(question: " Non-Persistence", answer: "The way the cloud is always in motion and particular services are usually never permanent"),
Flashcard(question: " Snapshot", answer: "Captures current configuration and data so if you want to recreate that instance later you can"),
Flashcard(question: " High Availability", answer: "Having devices that are always on and always available, more costly"),
Flashcard(question: " Usually in the order of restoration you restore the ___ first in order to restore the application", answer: "Database"),
Flashcard(question: " By using ___ of technology you can implement multiple security devices to better protect your system", answer: "Diversity"),
Flashcard(question: " Embedded System", answer: "Hardware and software designed for a specific function with a single task in mind (eg. traffic light controllers)"),
Flashcard(question: " SoC (System On a Chip)", answer: "Has multiple components on a single chip that handles multiple functions"),
Flashcard(question: " The downside to SoC is that it is difficult to upgrade ___", answer: "Hardware"),
Flashcard(question: " FPGA (Field-Programmable Gate Array)", answer: "Integrated circuit that you can program after the device is manufactured and shipping"),
Flashcard(question: " SCADA (Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition System)", answer: "Found in places with large amount of industrial equipment, used to modify configuration of equipment"),
Flashcard(question: " IoT (Internet of Things)", answer: "Devices that can be connected to many different types of systems in our homes and businesses"),
Flashcard(question: " VoIP (Voice Over Internet Protocol)", answer: "This technology is used to make telephone calls via the Internet usually at a cheaper cost, replaced analog phone lines"),
Flashcard(question: " It's common for HVAC to have a ___ that monitors all of the HVAC for the facility", answer: "Computer"),
Flashcard(question: " MFD (Multifunction Device)", answer: "Device that can do several things (eg. printer with scan, copy, fax, etc.)"),
Flashcard(question: " RTOS (Real Time Operating System)", answer: "Designed to work on a very deterministic schedule, eg. anti lock brakes on vehicles"),
Flashcard(question: " 5G can get speeds up to ___ per second", answer: "10 GB"),
Flashcard(question: " SIM (Subscriber Identity Module)", answer: "A small smart card that contains programming and information for small devices such as cell phones."),
Flashcard(question: " IMSI (International Mobile Subscriber Identity)", answer: "A unique number that represents the actual user associated with a particular SIM card"),
Flashcard(question: " Narrowband", answer: "Allowing communication across a very narrow range of frequencies; over longer distance, conserve freq. use"),
Flashcard(question: " Many ___ devices can communicate over long distances with narrowband", answer: "IoT"),
Flashcard(question: " Baseband", answer: "Using a single frequency to be able to communicate, generally single cable such as fiber or copper"),
Flashcard(question: " Baseband uses ___ of the bandwidth on that connection", answer: "All"),
Flashcard(question: " ZigBee", answer: "Alternative to WiFi and Bluetooth, communicates with IoT devices over longer distances using less power"),
Flashcard(question: " Mesh Network", answer: "Every device is connected directly to every other device in the network"),
Flashcard(question: " An issue with embedded systems is they usually run on a device that is not a ___ computer", answer: "Fully Capable"),
Flashcard(question: " Since embedded systems are out in the field, they might not have direct access to ___", answer: "Power Sources"),
Flashcard(question: " For embedded systems it is difficult to change or modify ___ features", answer: "Cryptography"),
Flashcard(question: " Embedded devices usually cannot add on an ___ functionality; they do one thing very well", answer: "Additional"),
Flashcard(question: " Access Control Vestibule", answer: "All doors can be locked or unlocked; opening one door causes others to lock"),
Flashcard(question: " Alarm", answer: "Circuit, duress or motion-based, used to inform of unauthorized access"),
Flashcard(question: " Industrial Camouflage", answer: "Concealing an important facility behind what is normally seen in a particular area"),
Flashcard(question: " One of the most reliable physical security features are ___", answer: "Security Guards"),
Flashcard(question: " Two-Person Integrity", answer: "Must have at least two people in the facility at all times, to monitor one another's actions"),
Flashcard(question: " Biometrics usually store a ___ of your fingerprint instead of the actual thing", answer: "Mathematical Representation"),
Flashcard(question: " Cable Locks", answer: "Used to secure portable computers, external hard drives, and other portable pieces of hardware to a table or other object"),
Flashcard(question: " USB Data Blocker", answer: "Hardware plug to prevent malicious data transfer when a device is plugged into a USB charging point"),
Flashcard(question: " ___ is a bad fire suppressant in cybersecurity because there is electronic equipment", answer: "Water"),
Flashcard(question: " Faraday Cage", answer: "A metallic enclosure that prevents the entry or escape of an electromagnetic field"),
Flashcard(question: " Screened Subnet", answer: "Formerly DMZ, uses firewall to prevent access to internal network"),
Flashcard(question: " PDS (Protected Distribution System)", answer: "Secured system of cable management to ensure that the wired network remains free from eavesdropping, tapping, data emanations, and other threats"),
Flashcard(question: " Air Gap", answer: "Separation between networks; prevents access between secure network and insecure network"),
Flashcard(question: " Most environments are on a ___ network", answer: "Shared"),
Flashcard(question: " There are extensive ___ in data centers since they generate a lot of heat", answer: "Cooling Systems"),
Flashcard(question: " Data centers have ___ and ___ aisles to blow air from the floor to conserve energy keeping equipment cool", answer: "Cold Hot"),
Flashcard(question: " Certificate of Destruction", answer: "Provided by a third party confirming they destroyed all the data or hardware"),
Flashcard(question: " Purge Data", answer: "Remove a single file or a section of data from an existing data store"),
Flashcard(question: " Wipe Data", answer: "Unrecoverable removal of data on a storage device"),
Flashcard(question: " Plaintext", answer: "An unencrypted message; in the clear"),
Flashcard(question: " Ciphertext", answer: "Encrypted message"),
Flashcard(question: " Cipher", answer: "The algorithm(s) needed to encrypt and decrypt a message"),
