Flashcard(question: " FileVault", answer: "A feature of Mac OS X that will encrypt all the files in the Home folder."),
Flashcard(question: " BitLocker", answer: "a microsoft utility to encrypt a drive"),
Flashcard(question: " Trust Platform Module (TPM)", answer: "chip residing on the motherboard that contains an encryption key"),
Flashcard(question: " Advanced Encryption Standard (AES)", answer: "Symmetric key encryption that supports 128-bit and 256-bit keys"),
Flashcard(question: " Hardware Security Module (HSM)", answer: "Physical devices that act as a secure cryptoprocessor during the encryption process"),
Flashcard(question: " Anti-virus (AV)", answer: "Software capable of detecting and removing virus infections and (in most cases) other types of malware, such as worms, Trojans, rootkits, adware, spyware, password crackers, network mappers, DoS tools, and others"),
