Flashcard(question: " Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR)", answer: "A software agent that collects system data and logs for analysis by a monitoring system to provide early detection of threats"),
Flashcard(question: " User and Entity Behavior Analytics (UEBA)", answer: "A system that can provide automated identification of suspicious activity by user accounts and computer hosts."),
Flashcard(question: " SIM", answer: "Integrated circuit that securely stores the international mobile subscriber identity (IMSI) number and its related key"),
Flashcard(question: " SIM Cloning", answer: "Allows two phones to utilize the same service and allows an attacker to gain access to the phone's data"),
Flashcard(question: " Bluejacking", answer: "sending unsolicited messages over bluetooth"),
Flashcard(question: " Bluesnarfing", answer: "Unauthorized access of information from a wireless device over a Bluetooth connection"),
Flashcard(question: " Remote Lock", answer: "Requires a PIN or password before someone can use the device"),
Flashcard(question: " Remote Wipe", answer: "Remotely erases the contents of the device to ensure the information is not recovered by the thief"),
Flashcard(question: " Mobile Device Management (MDM)", answer: "Centralized software solution that allows system administrators to create and enforce policies across its mobile devices"),
Flashcard(question: " Geotagging", answer: "Embedding of the geolocation into a piece of data (i.e photo)"),
Flashcard(question: " Storage Segmentation", answer: "Creating a clear separation between personal and company data on a single device"),
Flashcard(question: " step 1 mobile device hardening", answer: "update your device to the latest version of the software"),
Flashcard(question: " step 2 mobile device hardening", answer: "install antivirus"),
Flashcard(question: " step 3 mobile device hardening", answer: "train users on proper security and use of the device"),
Flashcard(question: " step 4 mobile device hardening", answer: "only install apps from the official mobile stores"),
Flashcard(question: " step 5 mobile device hardening", answer: "do not root or jailbreak your devices"),
Flashcard(question: " step 6 mobile device hardening", answer: "only use v2 SIM cards with your devices"),
Flashcard(question: " step 7 mobile device hardening", answer: "turn off all unnecessary features"),
Flashcard(question: " step 8 mobile device hardening", answer: "turn on encryption for voice and data"),
Flashcard(question: " step 9 mobile device hardening", answer: "use strong passwords or biometrics"),
Flashcard(question: " step 10 mobile device hardening", answer: "don't allow BYOD"),
Flashcard(question: " Hardening", answer: "Act of configuring an operating system securely by updating it, creating rules and policies to govern it, and removing unnecessary applications"),
Flashcard(question: " Least Functionality", answer: "Process of configuring workstation or server to only provide essential applications and services"),
Flashcard(question: " Application Allowlisting", answer: "Only applications that are on the list are allowed to be run by the operating system while all other applications are blocked"),
Flashcard(question: " Application Blocklisting", answer: "Any application placed on the list will prevented from running while all others will be permitted to run"),
Flashcard(question: " Trusted Operating System (TOS)", answer: "An operating system that meets the requirements set forth by government and has multilevel security"),
Flashcard(question: " Patches", answer: "A single problem-fixing piece of software for an operating system or application"),
Flashcard(question: " Security Update", answer: "Software code that is issued for a product-specific security-related vulnerability"),
Flashcard(question: " critical update", answer: "Software code for a specific problem addressing a critical, non-security bug in the software"),
Flashcard(question: " service pack", answer: "A tested, cumulative grouping of patches, hotfixes, security updates, critical updates, and possibly some feature or design changes"),
Flashcard(question: " windows update", answer: "Recommended update to fix a noncritical problem that users have found, as well as to provide additional features or capabilities"),
Flashcard(question: " driver update", answer: "Updated device driver to fix a security issue or add a feature to a supported piece of hardware"),
Flashcard(question: " patch management", answer: "Process of planning, testing, implementing, and auditing of software patches"),
Flashcard(question: " Group policy", answer: "A set of rules or policies that can be applied to a set of users or computer accounts within the operating system"),
Flashcard(question: " Baselining", answer: "Process of measuring changes in the network, hardware, and software environment"),
Flashcard(question: " NTFS", answer: "New Technology File System is the default file system format for Windows and is more secure because it supports logging, encryption, larger partition sizes, and larger file sizes than FAT32"),
Flashcard(question: " Due Diligence", answer: "A legal principle identifying a subject has used best practice or reasonable care when setting up, configuring, and maintaining a system"),
Flashcard(question: " Trusted Foundry", answer: "A microprocessor manufacturing utility that is part of a validated supply chain (one where hardware and software does not deviate from its documented function)"),
Flashcard(question: " Hardware Source Authenticity", answer: "The process of ensuring that hardware is procured tamper-free from trustworthy suppliers"),
Flashcard(question: " Hardware Root of Trust (ROT)", answer: "A cryptographic module embedded within a computer system that can endorse trusted execution and attest to boot settings and metrics"),
Flashcard(question: " Anti-tamper", answer: "Methods that make it difficult for an attacker to alter the authorized execution of software."),
Flashcard(question: " Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI)", answer: "A type of system firmware providing support for 64-bit CPU operation at boot, full GUI and mouse operation at boot, and better boot security."),
Flashcard(question: " Secure boot", answer: "A UEFI feature that prevents unwanted processes from executing during the boot operation."),
Flashcard(question: " Measured boot", answer: "A UEFI feature that gathers secure metrics to validate the boot process in an attestation report."),
Flashcard(question: " Attestation", answer: "A claim that the data presented in the report is valid by digitally signing it using the TPM's private key"),
Flashcard(question: " eFUSE", answer: "A means for software or firmware to permanently alter the state of a transistor on a computer chip"),
Flashcard(question: " trusted firmware updates", answer: "A firmware update that is digitally signed by the vendor and trusted by the system before installation"),
Flashcard(question: " secure processing", answer: "A mechanism for ensuring the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of software code and data as it is executed in volatile memory."),
Flashcard(question: " Processor Security Extensions", answer: "Low-level CPU changes and instructions that enable secure processing"),
Flashcard(question: " Trusted execution", answer: "The CPU's security extensions invoke a TPM and secure boot attestation to ensure that a trusted operating system is running"),
Flashcard(question: " Secure enclave", answer: "The extensions allow a trusted process to create an encrypted container for sensitive data"),
Flashcard(question: " Atomic Execution", answer: "Certain operations that should only be performed once or not at all, such as initializing a memory location"),
Flashcard(question: " bus encryption", answer: "Data is encrypted by an application prior to being placed on the data bus"),
Flashcard(question: " System virtual Machine", answer: "Complete platform designed to replace an entire physical computer and includes a full desktop/server operating system"),
Flashcard(question: " Processor virtual machine", answer: "Designed to only run a single process or application like a virtualized web browser or a simple web server"),
Flashcard(question: " Hypervisor", answer: "Manages the distribution of the physical resources of a host machine (server) to the virtual machines being run (guests)"),
